{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{bu.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Software as a service.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{7.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A tax of six percent is imposed upon the sales price from the sales, furnishing, or service of solid waste collection and disposal service.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(1)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For purposes of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fsolid waste\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means garbage, refuse, sludge from a water supply treatment plant or air contaminant treatment facility, and other discarded waste materials and sludges, in solid, semisolid, liquid, or contained gaseous form, resulting from nonresidential commercial operations, but does not include auto hulks; street sweepings; ash; construction debris; mining waste; trees; tires; lead acid batteries; used oil; hazardous waste; animal waste used as fertilizer; earthen fill, boulders, or rock; foundry sand used for daily cover at a sanitary landfill; sewage sludge; solid or dissolved material in domestic sewage or other common pollutants in water resources, such as silt, dissolved or suspended solids in industrial wastewater effluents or discharges which are point sources subject to permits under section 402 of the federal Water Pollution Control Act, or dissolved materials in irrigation return flows; or source, special nuclear, or by-product material defined by the federal Atomic Energy Act of 1954.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(2)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A recycling facility that separates or processes recyclable materials and that reduces the volume of the waste by at least eighty-five percent is exempt from the tax imposed by }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ if the waste exempted is collected and disposed of separately from other solid waste.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A person who transports solid waste generated by that person or another person without compensation shall pay the tax imposed by }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ at the collection or disposal facility based on the disposal charge or tipping fee. However, the costs of a service or portion of a service to collect and manage recyclable materials separated from solid waste by the waste generator are exempt from the tax imposed by }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{8.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A tax of six percent is imposed on the sales price from sales of bundled transactions. For the purposes of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, a }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fbundled transaction\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ is the retail sale of two or more distinct and identifiable products, except real property and services to real property, which are sold for one nonitemized price. A }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fbundled transaction\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ does not include the sale of any products in which the sales price varies, or is negotiable, based on the selection by the purchaser of the products included in the transaction.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fDistinct and identifiable products\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ does not include any of the following:}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(1)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Packaging or other materials that accompany the retail sale of the products and are incidental or immaterial to the retail sale of the products.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(2)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A product provided free of charge with the required purchase of another product. A product is }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fprovided free of charge\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ if the sales price of the product purchased does not vary depending on the inclusion of the product which is provided free of charge.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(3)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Items included in the definition of }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fsales price\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ pursuant to }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 423.1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{c.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fOne nonitemized price\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ does not include a price that is separately identified by product on binding sales or other supporting sales-related documentation made available to the customer in paper or electronic form.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{d.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A transaction that otherwise meets the definition of }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fbundled transaction\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ as defined in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ is not a bundled transaction if it is any of the following:}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(1)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The retail sale of tangible personal property or specified digital product and a service, where the tangible personal property or specified digital product is essential to the use of the service, and is provided exclusively in connection with the service, and the true object of the transaction is the service.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(2)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The retail sale of services where one service is provided that is essential to the use or receipt of a second service and the first service is provided exclusively in connection with the second service and the true object of the transaction is the second service.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(3)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(a)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A transaction that includes taxable products and nontaxable products and the purchase price or sales price of the taxable products is de minimis.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(b)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{For purposes of this subparagraph, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fde minimis\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means the seller\u8217\'3fs purchase or sales price of the taxable products is ten percent or less of the total purchase price or sales price of the bundled products. Sellers shall use either the purchase price or the sale price of the products to determine if the taxable products are de minimis. Sellers may not use a combination of the purchase price and sales price of the products to determine if the taxable products are de minimis.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(4)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The retail sale of exempt tangible personal property and taxable tangible personal property where all of the following apply:}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(a)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The transaction includes food and food ingredients, drugs, durable medical equipment, mobility enhancing equipment, prosthetic devices, or medical supplies.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(b)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The seller\u8217\'3fs purchase price or sales price of the taxable tangible personal property is fifty percent or less of the total purchase price or sales price of the bundled tangible personal property. Sellers may not use a combination of the purchase price and sales price of the tangible personal property when making the fifty percent determination for a transaction.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{9.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A tax of six percent is imposed upon the sales price from any mobile telecommunications service, including all paging services, that this state is allowed to tax pursuant to the provisions of the federal }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Mobile Telecommunications Sourcing Act}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Pub. L. No. 106-252}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{4 U.S.C. \'a7116 et seq.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ For purposes of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, taxes on mobile telecommunications service, as defined under the federal }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Mobile Telecommunications Sourcing Act}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ that are deemed to be provided by the customer\u8217\'3fs home service provider, shall be paid to the taxing jurisdiction whose territorial limits encompass the customer\u8217\'3fs place of primary use, regardless of where the mobile telecommunications service originates, terminates, or passes through and shall in all other respects be taxed in conformity with the federal }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Mobile Telecommunications Sourcing Act}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. All other provisions of the federal }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Mobile Telecommunications Sourcing Act}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ are adopted by the state of Iowa and incorporated into }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ by reference. With respect to mobile telecommunications service under the federal }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Mobile Telecommunications Sourcing Act}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, the director shall, if requested, enter into agreements consistent with the provisions of the federal Act.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{10.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A tax of six percent is imposed on the sales price of specified digital products sold at retail in the state. The tax applies whether the purchaser obtains permanent use or less than permanent use of the specified digital product, whether the sale is conditioned or not conditioned upon continued payment from the purchaser, and whether the sale is on a subscription basis or is not on a subscription basis.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The sale of a digital code that may be used to obtain or access a specified digital product shall be taxed in the same manner as the specified digital product. For purposes of this paragraph, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fdigital code\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means a method that permits a purchaser to obtain or access at a later date a specified digital product.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{11.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{All taxes collected under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this chapter}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ by a retailer or any individual are deemed to be held in trust for the state of Iowa.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{12.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The sales tax rate of six percent is reduced to five percent on January 1, 2051.}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2003 Acts, 1st Ex, ch 2, \'a795, 205}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2004 Acts, ch 1073, \'a724, 25}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2005 Acts, ch 140, \'a75, 18, 43}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2006 Acts, ch 1158, \'a770, 80}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2007 Acts, ch 119, \'a76}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2007 Acts, ch 186, \'a720}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2008 Acts, ch 1134, \'a74 \u8211\'3f 10, 36}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2010 Acts, ch 1145, \'a78, 9, 17}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2011 Acts, ch 25, \'a7143}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2011 Acts, ch 92, \'a75}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2012 Acts, ch 1017, \'a784}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2012 Acts, ch 1094, \'a717, 18}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2012 Acts, ch 1098, \'a72}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2013 Acts, ch 70, \'a711}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2013 Acts, ch 119, \'a79}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2013 Acts, ch 140, \'a7126}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2014 Acts, ch 1102, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2014 Acts, ch 1110, \'a74}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2014 Acts, ch 1127, \'a71, 3}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2015 Acts, ch 114, \'a71}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2015 Acts, ch 120, \'a721 \u8211\'3f 25}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2016 Acts, ch 1117, \'a72, 3}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2018 Acts, ch 1146, \'a71, 3, 4}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2018 Acts, ch 1161, \'a7169 \u8211\'3f 173, 229 \u8211\'3f 231}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2019 Acts, ch 152, \'a720, 21}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2019 Acts, ch 166, \'a77}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2020 Acts, ch 1118, \'a736, 37}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2021 Acts, ch 86, \'a752}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2022 Acts, ch 1138, \'a76}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2025 Acts, ch 148, \'a716}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a715J.2}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 15J.4}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 28A.17}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 29C.15}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 99B.27}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 321.105A}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 328.26}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 418.1}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 418.11}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 418.15}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 423.1}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 423.2A}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 423.3}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 423.4}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 423.5}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 423.6}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 423.14A}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 423.22}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 423.26}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 423.30}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 423.34}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 423.36}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 423.40}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 423.41}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 423C.3}}}{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{, 453E.4}}}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{Local sales and services tax, }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7423B.5}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj}{Subsection 1, paragraph b amended}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{423.2A}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E7_2E4_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E7_2E4_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Deposit and transfer of revenues.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{All revenues arising under the operation of the provisions of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subchapter II}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ shall be deposited into the general fund of the state.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Subsequent to the deposit into the general fund of the state, the director shall credit an amount equal to the product of the sales tax rate imposed in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 423.2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ times the sales price of the tangible personal property or services furnished to purchasers at a baseball and softball complex that has received an award under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 15F.207}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, Code 2019, and that meets the qualifications of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 423.4, subsection 10}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, into the baseball and softball complex sales tax rebate fund created under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 423.4, subsection 10}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fe\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. The director shall credit the moneys beginning the first day of the quarter following July 1, 2016. This paragraph is repealed thirty days following the date on which five million dollars in total rebates have been provided under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 423.4, subsection 10}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Subsequent to the deposit into the general fund of the state pursuant to }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, the department shall do the following in the order prescribed:}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Transfer the revenues collected under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ chapter 423B}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Transfer from the remaining revenues the amounts required under }}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cf5{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\cf5{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.legis.iowa.gov/docs/publications/icnst/402726.pdf#nameddest=iowaConst_art_VII_sec_10" }{\fldrslt \cf5 \f5 \fs18{{Article VII, section 10, of the Constitution of the State of Iowa}}}}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ to the natural resources and outdoor recreation trust fund created in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 461.31}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, if applicable.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{c.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Transfer one-sixth of the remaining revenues to the secure an advanced vision for education fund created in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 423F.2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. This paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fc\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ is repealed January 1, 2051.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{d.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Transfer to the baseball and softball complex sales tax rebate fund that portion of the sales tax receipts described in }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{subsection 1}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, paragraph }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fb\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, remaining after the transfers required under paragraphs }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fa\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fb\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, and }}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fc\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ of }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this subsection 2}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{. This paragraph is repealed thirty days following the date on which five million dollars in total rebates have been provided under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 423.4, subsection 10}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{e.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Beginning the first day of the calendar quarter beginning on the reinvestment district\u8217\'3fs commencement date, subject to remittance limitations established by the economic development authority board pursuant to }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 15J.4, subsection 3}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, transfer to a district account created in the state reinvestment district fund for each reinvestment district established under }}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{chapter 15J}